#: .\gb_items.json
msgid ""
"This is a scrap of synthetic bio-flesh. These were cultured in labs on an "
"industrial scale before the cataclysm for use in bio-synth robots. Even the "
"slightly electrical impusle can make this scrap of black, rubbery biomass "
"twitch and dance in your hands."
msgstr ""

#: .\gb_mobs.json
msgid "Salamander Mk.1"
msgid_plural "Salamander Mk.1s"
msgstr[0] ""
msgstr[1] ""

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Salamander Mk.1'}
#: .\gb_mobs.json
msgid ""
"For years, various defense contractors and roboticists puzzled over one "
"simple question: what is the best form of locomotion for large robotic "
"vehicle? Various methods of movement were suggested until one Boston "
"Dynamics engineer suggested eschewing electro-mechanical treads or wheels in"
" favor of bio-synethic legs. The Salamander Mk.I was his brainchild: large "
"bipedal hybrid robots used as a form of riot control by law enforcement."
msgstr ""

